1
00:00:04,005 --> 00:00:05,639
(Luna) This is the location where the ``Sonezaki Shinju'' took place.

2
00:00:05,706 --> 00:00:09,043
⟨A housewife who was cheated on by her husband and a bar mom who is a literary geek →

3
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:12,546
Fulfilling a fateful encounter ⟩ Ah, that's tough!

4
00:00:12,613 --> 00:00:16,550
⟨During a trip to Osaka, a suicide incident occurred in Sonezaki →

5
00:00:16,617 --> 00:00:19,053
Two people solve the problem with literary knowledge⟩

6
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:21,055
(Luna) We are connected.

7
00:00:21,122 --> 00:00:23,557
(Ryoko) It was my first and last true love.

8
00:00:23,624 --> 00:00:27,061
(Luna) We will collect the information necessary to search for Kazuto-san.

9
00:00:27,128 --> 00:00:33,567
⟨Luna and Ryoko finally set out to find Kazuto in earnest⟩

10
00:00:33,634 --> 00:00:36,070
(Ryoko) What do you look up at the library?

11
00:00:36,137 --> 00:00:39,073
(Luna) French writer Patrick Modiano is →

12
00:00:39,140 --> 00:00:41,575
Did you know? (Ryoko) Of course I don't know.

13
00:00:41,642 --> 00:00:45,579
(Luna) In his work "Don't get lost around here"→

14
00:00:45,646 --> 00:00:47,581
Based on the address book I found →

15
00:00:47,648 --> 00:00:50,084
There will be an episode about searching for someone.

16
00:00:50,151 --> 00:00:52,586
Using that as a hint, use an old phone book →

17
00:00:52,653 --> 00:00:55,089
I'm trying to find Kazuto-san's whereabouts.

18
00:00:55,156 --> 00:00:57,591
If you can't find it even after searching on SNS →

19
00:00:57,658 --> 00:01:01,095
We have no choice but to do it steadily. (Ryoko) SNS?

20
00:01:01,162 --> 00:01:04,031
(Luna) Ryoko, you have done some research, right?

21
00:01:04,098 --> 00:01:07,034
(Ryoko) Eh, how do you know?

22
00:01:07,101 --> 00:01:14,041
(Luna) In this day and age, is there anyone who hasn't searched for their ex-lover on SNS?

23
00:01:14,108 --> 00:01:16,544
(Ryoko) I've said it...

24
00:01:16,610 --> 00:01:22,049
Kazuto Sato, who lives in Osaka, did a search and found about 20 people.

25
00:01:22,116 --> 00:01:24,552
But it didn't seem like everyone was Kazuto.

26
00:01:24,618 --> 00:01:28,556
(Luna) Eh, Kazuto-san is Sato-san?

27
00:01:28,622 --> 00:01:30,558
(Ryoko) Yes, but.

28
00:01:30,624 --> 00:01:33,060
(Luna) The most common surname in Japan...｡

29
00:01:33,127 --> 00:01:35,563
Kazuto-san is inheriting his parents' family, right?

30
00:01:35,629 --> 00:01:37,565
What kind of business are you doing?

31
00:01:37,631 --> 00:01:41,068
(Ryoko) I don't understand, except that I am inheriting my parents' family business.

32
00:01:41,135 --> 00:01:44,071
(Luna) I see. For now...

33
00:01:44,138 --> 00:01:48,576
(Luna's voice) The company name with Sato's name and the last name Sato are better →

34
00:01:48,642 --> 00:01:51,078
List the companies you represent.

35
00:01:51,145 --> 00:01:53,080
Go around there one by one→

36
00:01:53,147 --> 00:01:58,085
I think the safest way is to ask if they know Mr. Custom.

37
00:01:58,152 --> 00:02:01,088
(Ryoko) There are 30 applicable hotels.

38
00:02:01,155 --> 00:02:03,524
Are you going to do all this directly?

39
00:02:03,591 --> 00:02:07,528
(Luna) Yes, they probably won't tell you if you call them.

40
00:02:07,595 --> 00:02:11,532
(Ryoko) But wouldn't it be suspicious if someone suddenly barged in?

41
00:02:11,599 --> 00:02:16,036
(Luna) It's okay, I have an idea.

42
00:02:16,103 --> 00:02:19,540
Let's think about an efficient route.

43
00:02:19,607 --> 00:02:22,610
(Ryoko) What, this star symbol...?

44
00:02:24,612 --> 00:02:27,548
Oh, maybe it's a literary spot?

45
00:02:27,615 --> 00:02:30,050
(Luna) It's just a side note.

46
00:02:30,117 --> 00:02:32,553
(Ryoko) By the way, hehe...｡

47
00:02:32,620 --> 00:02:35,556
(Luna) The atmosphere in the library is great.

48
00:02:35,623 --> 00:02:40,561
Even if you go every day, you won't be able to read all the books here.

49
00:02:40,628 --> 00:02:44,565
I wish I had 200 more years to live.

50
00:02:44,632 --> 00:02:50,070
(Ryoko) It's been a long time since I was in university.

51
00:02:50,137 --> 00:02:52,573
(Luna) Like when you're studying for an exam?

52
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:55,075
(Ryoko) Kazuto was the one studying.

53
00:02:55,142 --> 00:02:57,645
(Ryoko's voice) It was a meeting place.

54
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:12,092
(Ryoko) [Kazuto]

55
00:03:14,595 --> 00:03:17,531
[Thank you for waiting] (Custom) [Thank you]

56
00:03:17,598 --> 00:03:20,534
(Ryoko) [Sorry for keeping you waiting] (Custom) [Uh]

57
00:03:20,601 --> 00:03:24,538
[I'm just waiting because I want to meet Ryoko]

58
00:03:24,605 --> 00:03:26,607
(Ryoko) [Yes, yes]

59
00:03:30,611 --> 00:03:32,613
(Ryoko) [Hehe...]

60
00:03:34,114 --> 00:03:38,052
[Are you making progress in studying for the exam? 〕 >> 〔Hmm, what do you think?〕

61
00:03:38,118 --> 00:03:41,055
[If Dazai was the subject of the exam, I could afford it.]

62
00:03:41,121 --> 00:03:44,558
(Ryoko) [Hehe... Kazuto will definitely pass]

63
00:03:44,625 --> 00:03:46,560
>> [I hope so]

64
00:03:46,627 --> 00:03:49,063
(Ryoko) [Graduate school?]

65
00:03:49,129 --> 00:03:52,566
[That's amazing] >> [What I like is →

66
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:55,569
It makes me want to dig into it to the hilt.]

67
00:03:55,636 --> 00:03:59,640
(Ryoko's voice) Kazuto liked Osamu Dazai.

68
00:04:01,141 --> 00:04:03,510
(Custom) [Hmm? ] (Ryoko) [Look, it's a good shot]

69
00:04:03,577 --> 00:04:05,512
>> [It's true] (Ryoko) [Isn't it good? ]

70
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:09,016
(Ryoko's voice) I don't know anything about literature, though.

71
00:04:09,083 --> 00:04:12,019
(ルナ) Mr. Dazai…｡

72
00:04:12,086 --> 00:04:15,589
I'm starting to get interested in Kazuto.

73
00:04:18,592 --> 00:04:23,097
(Ryoko) I feel like I'll be able to get along with mom quickly.

74
00:04:27,101 --> 00:04:29,103
(Luna) Let's cross here.

75
00:04:31,105 --> 00:04:33,540
(Ryoko) Michi Shucho?

76
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:36,110
(Luna) It's pronounced "Doshomachi."

77
00:04:37,611 --> 00:04:42,049
During the Edo period, it had a monopoly over the distribution of medicines →

78
00:04:42,116 --> 00:04:44,551
It is called the ``Medicine Town.''

79
00:04:44,618 --> 00:04:47,554
Doshomachi is still home to the headquarters of major pharmaceutical companies →

80
00:04:47,621 --> 00:04:49,556
Many have gathered.

81
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:51,625
(Ryoko) Hey.

82
00:04:54,128 --> 00:04:56,630
(Luna) Yes, Sato tableware.

83
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:01,068
(Luna) Hello.

84
00:05:01,135 --> 00:05:04,071
>> Welcome, please take a look.

85
00:05:10,077 --> 00:05:13,013
(Luna) Wow~ This tumbler is wonderful.

86
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:15,082
Please click here.

87
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,018
(Ryoko) Eh, 50,000!?

88
00:05:18,085 --> 00:05:21,021
>> Thank you. How many customers do you need?

89
00:05:21,088 --> 00:05:24,024
(Luna) I want to put it in the store, so... 20 customers then.

90
00:05:24,091 --> 00:05:26,026
(Ryoko) Ni...!?

91
00:05:26,093 --> 00:05:28,028
50,000 times 20...

92
00:05:28,095 --> 00:05:30,531
Yeah~｡

93
00:05:30,597 --> 00:05:34,034
>> Please fill in here. (Luna) Yes.

94
00:05:34,101 --> 00:05:36,537
I would like to ask you something unexpected.→

95
00:05:36,603 --> 00:05:39,540
Do you know someone called Kazuto Sato?

96
00:05:39,606 --> 00:05:41,542
>> Kazuto Sato?

97
00:05:41,608 --> 00:05:45,546
(Luna) She is 45 years old and graduated from the Faculty of Letters at Eisei University →

98
00:05:45,612 --> 00:05:48,549
I played baseball in high school.

99
00:05:48,615 --> 00:05:50,551
I'm an old acquaintance →

100
00:05:50,617 --> 00:05:54,621
I heard that your family is doing business in Osaka.

101
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:02,062
>> We don't have anyone like that in our house.

102
00:06:02,129 --> 00:06:04,064
(Ryoko) Is that so?

103
00:06:05,566 --> 00:06:08,001
(Luna) Hello, Bubbly-chan?

104
00:06:08,068 --> 00:06:12,005
The package will arrive around next week, so please pick it up.

105
00:06:12,072 --> 00:06:15,576
I'm looking forward to this very nice tumbler.

106
00:06:17,077 --> 00:06:21,582
(Ryoko) It's a strategy to buy products and make money.

107
00:06:26,086 --> 00:06:29,523
(Luna) Then, here and here, please.

108
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:31,525
Perfect for my shop!

109
00:06:31,592 --> 00:06:34,027
>> Thank you. (Ryoko) Eh!?

110
00:06:34,094 --> 00:06:37,030
(Luna) I would like to ask you to renovate the store.

111
00:06:37,097 --> 00:06:40,534
The budget is... 20 million.

112
00:06:40,601 --> 00:06:43,537
(Salesperson) Thank you.

113
00:06:43,604 --> 00:06:46,039
(Luna) Kazuto-san, I can't find it.

114
00:06:46,106 --> 00:06:50,043
(Ryoko) Hey, it's impossible to buy too much. Stop it already.

115
00:06:50,110 --> 00:06:53,046
(Luna) I'm just buying what I need for the store.

116
00:06:53,113 --> 00:06:57,551
It's not for Ryoko, so don't worry.

117
00:06:57,618 --> 00:07:01,054
(Ryoko) Maybe this cost is also darling?

118
00:07:01,121 --> 00:07:03,056
(Luna) What do you think?

119
00:07:03,123 --> 00:07:04,992
(Ryoko) Huh…｡

120
00:07:05,058 --> 00:07:07,995
I feel like it's reckless after all.

121
00:07:08,061 --> 00:07:10,497
I didn't expect Kazuto to be found this way...

122
00:07:10,564 --> 00:07:15,502
(Luna) There are only 5 houses left, 25 more to come.

123
00:07:15,569 --> 00:07:19,006
(Ryoko) Eh... Eh, this is →

124
00:07:19,072 --> 00:07:21,508
Wouldn't it be faster to ask a detective?

125
00:07:21,575 --> 00:07:24,511
(Luna) Isn't that kind of tasteless?

126
00:07:24,578 --> 00:07:28,015
(Ryoko) It would take more time and effort to hire a professional...

127
00:07:28,081 --> 00:07:30,017
(Luna) Let's go next.

128
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,519
⟨The search for Kazuto has many challenges ahead⟩

129
00:07:32,586 --> 00:07:34,521
⟨Moreover, after this→

130
00:07:34,588 --> 00:07:38,025
An incredible incident awaited us⟩

131
00:07:38,091 --> 00:07:42,596
♪～

132
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:52,105
(Tamura) We are continuing to ask people around us →

133
00:07:52,172 --> 00:07:54,274
There are no sightings reported at this time.

134
00:07:54,341 --> 00:07:56,777
(Kominato) It's a pain that there's no camera protection on site.

135
00:07:56,844 --> 00:07:58,779
(Detective) The murder weapon hasn't been released yet.

136
00:07:58,846 --> 00:08:01,281
(Chief of the Criminal Investigation Division) Are you going to search Tosahorikawa as well?

137
00:08:01,348 --> 00:08:03,283
Let's expand the scope of land acquisition.

138
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,786
I wonder if Luna will help me again.

139
00:08:05,853 --> 00:08:07,788
(Tamura) Who is it?

140
00:08:07,855 --> 00:08:10,290
Ah Noppy. >> Noppy Noppy.

141
00:08:10,357 --> 00:08:12,292
I wonder how long those two will be here?

142
00:08:12,359 --> 00:08:13,861
(Tamura) Now?

143
00:08:15,863 --> 00:08:18,365
(Ryoko) "Sato Shokai"...

144
00:08:27,374 --> 00:08:29,877
(Luna) I'm sorry.

145
00:08:31,879 --> 00:08:33,814
(Male) Yes.

146
00:08:33,881 --> 00:08:36,316
(Luna) I would like to see the cloth.

147
00:08:36,383 --> 00:08:37,818
>>Ah...｡

148
00:08:37,885 --> 00:08:40,888
(Yoriko) Mr. Ichigo refuses.

149
00:08:42,389 --> 00:08:46,326
(Yoriko) I can't see it, but I can't tell by the voice.

150
00:08:46,393 --> 00:08:48,328
I beg you, come back.

151
00:08:48,395 --> 00:08:51,832
(Male) Sorry, grandma seems to be in a really bad mood today.

152
00:08:51,899 --> 00:08:53,767
(Yoriko) Are you still on?

153
00:08:53,834 --> 00:08:56,770
Get out quickly! Look!

154
00:08:56,837 --> 00:08:59,273
(Male) I'm really sorry, please come back again.

155
00:08:59,339 --> 00:09:03,343
(Yoriko) Nori-kun, the shop has already closed.

156
00:09:10,851 --> 00:09:12,786
Is it okay for the customer to go home?

157
00:09:12,853 --> 00:09:16,790
Yes, I can't do it today.

158
00:09:16,857 --> 00:09:18,792
(Male) Yes.

159
00:09:18,859 --> 00:09:20,794
Hey, grandma. (Yoriko) Huh?

160
00:09:20,861 --> 00:09:22,863
(Male) I'm not sure what I want to ask.

161
00:09:23,864 --> 00:09:27,801
(Ryoko) Even mom's hands won't work with someone who doesn't intend to sell.

162
00:09:27,868 --> 00:09:31,305
(Luna) Let's change the time and start again. (Ryoko) Yeah.

163
00:09:31,371 --> 00:09:35,809
But kimono shops have a unique smell.

164
00:09:35,876 --> 00:09:37,811
(Luna) Is it a scent bag?

165
00:09:37,878 --> 00:09:40,814
Enjoy the scent by slipping it into your kimono obi →

166
00:09:40,881 --> 00:09:44,818
It also has an insect repellent effect. (Ryoko) That's right.

167
00:09:44,885 --> 00:09:48,822
That young man's grandson?

168
00:09:48,889 --> 00:09:52,392
...It also smelled good.

169
00:09:54,394 --> 00:09:55,829
Huh…｡

170
00:09:55,896 --> 00:09:59,833
My husband would sometimes come home smelling like perfume →

171
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:02,402
I've become sensitive to smells.

172
00:10:04,404 --> 00:10:06,406
Ah...

173
00:10:09,910 --> 00:10:13,914
(Luna) You're the writer in charge of your husband...right?

174
00:10:16,917 --> 00:10:20,921
(Ryoko) Huh... can't you talk about other people?

175
00:10:24,424 --> 00:10:28,362
(Ryoko) Mom, you said that when we first met, right?

176
00:10:28,428 --> 00:10:30,864
I guess so too.

177
00:10:30,931 --> 00:10:32,866
That's true.

178
00:10:32,933 --> 00:10:35,369
While complaining about my husband's cheating →

179
00:10:35,435 --> 00:10:39,439
I'm also looking for Kazuto like this.

180
00:10:41,441 --> 00:10:46,380
(Luna) People can't live that rightly.

181
00:10:46,446 --> 00:10:51,451
Sometimes it's sloppy or weak.

182
00:11:10,137 --> 00:11:14,508
(sound of deep breathing)

183
00:11:14,574 --> 00:11:17,511
(Ryoko) What are you doing? (Luna) Ah...

184
00:11:17,577 --> 00:11:22,516
I wanted to breathe in the same air that Oshi breathed in.

185
00:11:22,582 --> 00:11:26,520
Ryoko-san, can I take a short detour?

186
00:11:26,586 --> 00:11:29,523
(Ryoko) That's your intention from the beginning, right?

187
00:11:29,589 --> 00:11:31,525
Who is your favorite?

188
00:11:31,591 --> 00:11:34,027
(Luna) This is Junichiro Tanizaki.

189
00:11:34,094 --> 00:11:37,030
Ah!

190
00:11:37,097 --> 00:11:40,033
Ah! There it was!

191
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:44,104
Ah~ Mr. Tanizaki's handwriting!

192
00:11:45,105 --> 00:11:47,040
(Ryoko) “Shunkinsho”…｡

193
00:11:47,107 --> 00:11:51,545
(Luna) Doshomachi is the town where "Shunkinsho" was set.

194
00:11:51,611 --> 00:11:57,484
Ah~ Mr. Tanizaki writes like this.

195
00:11:57,551 --> 00:12:00,053
Please excuse me.

196
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:03,490
📱(Camera shutter sound)

197
00:12:03,557 --> 00:12:06,493
(Ryoko) Can I say something very obvious?

198
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,495
(Luna) Yes.

199
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:12,999
(Ryoko) When you actually see handwritten letters like this→

200
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:17,504
Novels are actually written by real people.

201
00:12:17,571 --> 00:12:21,508
Haha, sorry for saying something stupid.

202
00:12:21,575 --> 00:12:26,580
(Luna) No, I think that sensitivity is wonderful.

203
00:12:28,081 --> 00:12:31,017
(Ryoko) What kind of story is “Shunkinsho”?

204
00:12:31,084 --> 00:12:33,520
(Luna) Good to hear from you.

205
00:12:33,587 --> 00:12:37,524
It's a story of ultimate love.

206
00:12:37,591 --> 00:12:41,027
Blind shamisen player Shunkin.

207
00:12:41,094 --> 00:12:44,531
Despite her beauty, which seems out of this world, she can be as selfish as she wants.

208
00:12:44,598 --> 00:12:49,035
There is one man who will be there for her and be her hands and feet.

209
00:12:49,102 --> 00:12:51,037
His name is Sasuke, a servant.

210
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:53,974
Whether you get cursed at or kicked →

211
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:56,476
The only thing I can do is be by Shunkoto's side →

212
00:12:56,543 --> 00:12:59,980
Sasuke couldn't have been happier.

213
00:13:00,046 --> 00:13:03,483
However, one night, Shunkin was stolen by someone →

214
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:06,486
Her unparalleled beauty is bathed in boiling water→

215
00:13:06,553 --> 00:13:08,989
It was brutally burnt.

216
00:13:09,055 --> 00:13:11,992
``I don't want to show this to anyone.''

217
00:13:12,058 --> 00:13:15,495
Sasuke senses Shunkoto's heart as she breaks down in tears.

218
00:13:15,562 --> 00:13:17,998
To be close to the heart of the woman I love→

219
00:13:18,064 --> 00:13:21,001
He sticks a needle in his own eye!

220
00:13:21,067 --> 00:13:24,504
This is the man who continued to devote himself with single-minded passion→

221
00:13:24,571 --> 00:13:28,008
Sasuke's salvation and beyond common sense →

222
00:13:28,074 --> 00:13:32,012
It was the ultimate love.

223
00:13:32,078 --> 00:13:34,514
(Ryoko) No, it's scary.

224
00:13:34,581 --> 00:13:38,518
Did Sasuke need to hurt himself?

225
00:13:38,585 --> 00:13:41,521
Wouldn't it have been better to just pretend that I couldn't see?

226
00:13:41,588 --> 00:13:46,026
(Luna) I want to keep the beautiful Shunkin in my memory forever →

227
00:13:46,092 --> 00:13:48,528
There may have been an aspect of...

228
00:13:48,595 --> 00:13:52,032
Either way, that's Sasuke's love.

229
00:13:52,098 --> 00:13:54,968
I had such strong feelings.

230
00:13:55,035 --> 00:13:58,471
A life-threatening passion.

231
00:13:58,538 --> 00:14:01,041
(Ryoko) Risking my life...｡

232
00:14:03,543 --> 00:14:05,478
Ah...｡

233
00:14:05,545 --> 00:14:11,484
The apartment I lived in when I was a university student caught fire.

234
00:14:11,551 --> 00:14:13,486
(Custom) [Ryoko! ] (Ryoko) [coughing]

235
00:14:13,553 --> 00:14:16,990
(Ryoko's voice) Kazuto jumped in. >> [Ryoko! Ryoko! ]

236
00:14:17,057 --> 00:14:18,491
(Ryoko) [Kazuto...]

237
00:14:18,558 --> 00:14:19,993
>> [Because it's okay now]

238
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:22,495
(Ryoko) [coughing] >> [Hmm! Can you stand? ]

239
00:14:22,562 --> 00:14:25,565
(Ryoko) [Coughing] >> [Coughing]

240
00:14:28,068 --> 00:14:34,007
(Ryoko's voice) The next day, Kazuto was supposed to take the entrance exam for graduate school.

241
00:14:34,074 --> 00:14:38,011
[I'm sorry... I'm sorry...]

242
00:14:38,078 --> 00:14:42,015
>> [Ryoko, don't cry anymore]

243
00:14:42,082 --> 00:14:45,018
[You can take the entrance exam again]

244
00:14:45,085 --> 00:14:47,087
(Ryoko) [But...]

245
00:14:50,090 --> 00:14:58,031
>> [Love is risking your life, I don't think it's naive]

246
00:14:59,532 --> 00:15:03,036
[...Is that too cool?]

247
00:15:06,039 --> 00:15:08,475
(Ryoko's voice) Kazuto told me.

248
00:15:08,541 --> 00:15:12,979
``To love is to risk your life.''

249
00:15:13,046 --> 00:15:18,485
(Luna) A passage from Osamu Dazai's ``Female ni ni te''.

250
00:15:18,551 --> 00:15:21,054
He's a wonderful person.

251
00:15:22,555 --> 00:15:24,557
(Ryoko) But...

252
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:29,496
Ah... ugh.

253
00:15:29,562 --> 00:15:33,066
Hey, aren't you hungry? Let's eat rice.

254
00:15:38,071 --> 00:15:40,073
📱(Camera shutter sound)

255
00:15:48,281 --> 00:15:49,749
(sipping sound)

256
00:15:49,816 --> 00:15:51,251
(Ryoko) Delicious!

257
00:15:51,318 --> 00:15:54,688
Hey, this dregs is fried hormones, right?

258
00:15:54,754 --> 00:15:58,692
(Luna) Cow small intestine is high in protein and low in fat →

259
00:15:58,758 --> 00:16:01,194
A beauty ingredient rich in collagen.

260
00:16:01,261 --> 00:16:05,699
>> Yes, please wait for the quick meal. (Luna) I'm sorry.

261
00:16:05,765 --> 00:16:08,702
(Ryoko) Wow~ The food looks delicious too!

262
00:16:08,768 --> 00:16:10,270
Ah!

263
00:16:11,771 --> 00:16:13,273
📱(vibration sound)

264
00:16:16,276 --> 00:16:19,713
(Ryoko's voice) ``If you run out of rice, go to the rice shop across the station →

265
00:16:19,779 --> 00:16:23,216
Please buy it, it's expensive at the supermarket."

266
00:16:23,283 --> 00:16:27,220
(Atsushi's voice) ``I don't know how to cook the rice I buy in packs.''

267
00:16:27,287 --> 00:16:31,224
(Ryoko) No, packs are expensive.

268
00:16:31,291 --> 00:16:33,727
(Luna) Excuse me. (Ryoko) Huh?

269
00:16:33,793 --> 00:16:38,732
Ah, wait... (Luna) ``If you search for how to cook rice→

270
00:16:38,798 --> 00:16:42,235
I think some will come out.”

271
00:16:42,302 --> 00:16:43,737
Send. (Ryoko) Ah!

272
00:16:43,803 --> 00:16:45,739
(Luna) My son is already a high school student →

273
00:16:45,805 --> 00:16:49,743
Not knowing how to cook rice is a serious problem.

274
00:16:49,809 --> 00:16:51,745
(Ryoko) Huh…｡ 📱(Reception sound)

275
00:16:51,811 --> 00:16:53,747
(Atsushi's voice) "Grandma, are you okay?"

276
00:16:53,813 --> 00:16:55,682
"Maybe you should take me to the hospital."

277
00:16:55,749 --> 00:16:57,183
(Ryoko) Ah...

278
00:16:57,250 --> 00:17:00,687
Right now, I'm taking care of my grandmother who has a strained back.

279
00:17:00,754 --> 00:17:03,189
Because I'm supposed to be staying the night.

280
00:17:03,256 --> 00:17:06,693
(Luna) ``He's gradually getting better...''

281
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:10,697
(Ryoko) Hey, hey! (Luna) "There's no need to worry."

282
00:17:10,764 --> 00:17:14,200
Send It's okay now.

283
00:17:14,267 --> 00:17:17,270
(Ryoko) The tone is too different.

284
00:17:19,773 --> 00:17:22,709
Atsushi is a grandmother's child.

285
00:17:22,776 --> 00:17:28,715
She's usually unfriendly, but she has a kind heart.

286
00:17:28,782 --> 00:17:31,284
(Luna) What a wonderful family.

287
00:17:35,288 --> 00:17:38,224
(Tamura) Ah. >> Ah, Luna!

288
00:17:38,291 --> 00:17:40,727
(General) Welcome! (Kominato) General: Two pieces of Kasu udon.

289
00:17:40,794 --> 00:17:42,729
(General) Hey, are you going to have a set meal today?

290
00:17:42,796 --> 00:17:45,231
(Kominato) Is it okay? (Tamura) There are others available, right?

291
00:17:45,298 --> 00:17:49,736
(Kominato) Excuse me. (Ryoko) Um... Mr. Tamura and Mr. Kominato.

292
00:17:49,803 --> 00:17:52,739
>> Thank you very much for everything you did the other day.

293
00:17:52,806 --> 00:17:56,242
(Luna) Are you in a hurry today? (Tamura) Huh?

294
00:17:56,309 --> 00:17:59,245
(Luna) The general says we should have a set meal today.

295
00:17:59,312 --> 00:18:03,750
>> As expected, you are still as helpful as ever.

296
00:18:03,817 --> 00:18:06,753
(Monitor) (Caster) Inside the Osawado Pawnshop in Doshomachi →

297
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:10,757
A man was found dead, bleeding from the head.

298
00:18:10,824 --> 00:18:15,261
(Luna) Are you following that case? (Tamura) Eh, why?

299
00:18:15,328 --> 00:18:17,764
Ah, Kominato-san, no way...

300
00:18:17,831 --> 00:18:20,266
>> No, I didn't say anything. I didn't say anything.

301
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:22,769
(Luna) I just thought you might see Mr. Tamura's face.

302
00:18:22,836 --> 00:18:24,771
>> Isn't it you? (Monitor) On the head of the victim, Mr. Osawa →

303
00:18:24,838 --> 00:18:27,774
There were signs of being hit with something like a blunt object.

304
00:18:27,841 --> 00:18:31,778
No murder weapon was found near the scene.

305
00:18:31,845 --> 00:18:34,781
(Luna) A blunt weapon... Hasn't the murder weapon been found yet?

306
00:18:34,848 --> 00:18:36,850
>> Ah...｡ (coughs)

307
00:18:37,851 --> 00:18:43,790
>> Ah, hmm... Speaking of murder weapons that are common in mystery novels →

308
00:18:43,857 --> 00:18:47,293
Socks filled with ice or stones.

309
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:49,796
What else do you have?

310
00:18:49,863 --> 00:18:53,299
(Luna) In Roald Dahl's work "The Gentle Weapon" →

311
00:18:53,366 --> 00:18:56,236
It was frozen sheep meat. >> Ah, that's interesting.

312
00:18:56,302 --> 00:18:58,238
(Ryoko) Ah, in “Ninsaburo Furuhata” →

313
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:02,242
There was an incident where someone was beaten to death with a large amount of coins in a bag, right?

314
00:19:02,308 --> 00:19:04,744
(Tamura) Yes, there was. (Kominato) Huh, you know me very well.

315
00:19:04,811 --> 00:19:07,747
(Ryoko) I don't read books, but I like dramas.

316
00:19:07,814 --> 00:19:10,750
(Luna) Mr. Tamura used to imitate people when he was in high school.

317
00:19:10,817 --> 00:19:13,253
>> Ah, just Tamura? (Tamura) It doesn't matter.

318
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:15,755
(Ryoko) Maybe that's why you became a detective? (Tamura) That doesn't matter either.

319
00:19:15,822 --> 00:19:20,260
>> Haha I think ``Dadfly Detective'' Taka and Yuji are so cool~.

320
00:19:20,326 --> 00:19:22,762
(Ryoko) I was watching it on a rebroadcast! >> Ah, I see.

321
00:19:22,829 --> 00:19:25,765
(Luna) Ah! (Ryoko) What... what happened?

322
00:19:25,832 --> 00:19:30,270
(Luna) A photo of the stone monument of ``Shunkinsho''...

323
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:32,272
(Ryoko) Yeah, what is this?

324
00:19:32,338 --> 00:19:36,276
(Luna) The text on the handwritten manuscript is so blurry that I can't read it!

325
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:41,781
(Ryoko) Ah~ Mama, I was shaking with emotion at that time.

326
00:19:41,848 --> 00:19:43,283
(Luna) Ah~｡

327
00:19:43,349 --> 00:19:45,785
(Ryoko) Let's go again later. We'll hang out.

328
00:19:45,852 --> 00:19:49,289
(Luna) Really? thank you.

329
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:53,293
>> Is the purpose of your trip this time to visit famous literary sites?

330
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:56,729
(Luna) No, I'm looking for someone. (Tamura) Looking for someone?

331
00:19:56,796 --> 00:19:59,232
(Luna) I'm looking for Ryoko's acquaintances.

332
00:19:59,299 --> 00:20:01,234
>> Ah, is that so?

333
00:20:01,301 --> 00:20:04,237
Please let me know if I can be of any assistance.

334
00:20:04,304 --> 00:20:05,738
(Ryoko) Thank you.

335
00:20:05,805 --> 00:20:10,743
>> Yes, sorry for keeping you waiting for two Kasu udon noodles.

336
00:20:10,810 --> 00:20:14,247
(Luna) Excuse me, can I have some special pudding? (General) Special pudding.

337
00:20:14,314 --> 00:20:17,750
(Luna) What about Ryoko? (Ryoko) Ah, then I'll just have regular pudding.

338
00:20:17,817 --> 00:20:19,252
(General) Ordinary pudding OK.

339
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:21,254
(Tamura) Noppi: I've always liked sweets.

340
00:20:21,321 --> 00:20:23,756
(Luna) Because I'm a girl. >> That's right.

341
00:20:23,823 --> 00:20:25,758
(sound of slurping udon)

342
00:20:25,825 --> 00:20:30,263
(Tamura) General, thank you for the meal. >> Yes, thank you. 1800 yen.

343
00:20:30,330 --> 00:20:32,265
Then we'll go first.

344
00:20:32,332 --> 00:20:35,335
(Ryoko) Thank you for your hard work in the cold. (Luna) Good day.

345
00:20:36,836 --> 00:20:38,838
Looks delicious.

346
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:44,277
Mmm, delicious. (Ryoko) Hehehe...｡

347
00:20:44,344 --> 00:20:46,779
Hey, can I ask you something?

348
00:20:46,846 --> 00:20:48,781
(Luna) Whatever.

349
00:20:48,848 --> 00:20:54,721
(Ryoko) Mom, when did you realize that you were a woman?

350
00:20:54,787 --> 00:20:58,725
(Luna) Hmm... (Ryoko) Ah, I'm sorry.

351
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:02,228
You don't listen to things like this very often.

352
00:21:02,295 --> 00:21:05,231
(Luna) Ah, no, it doesn't really matter.

353
00:21:05,298 --> 00:21:07,734
I don't know about other people though →

354
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:10,803
I get asked this question all the time at stores.

355
00:21:12,305 --> 00:21:16,743
I first became aware of this clearly when I was in junior high school.

356
00:21:16,809 --> 00:21:20,246
It all started when I felt uncomfortable wearing school uniforms.

357
00:21:20,313 --> 00:21:24,250
I changed my family register in my early 20s.

358
00:21:24,317 --> 00:21:28,254
I also wanted to eliminate my own discomfort →

359
00:21:28,321 --> 00:21:32,258
I want to be recognized by society based on the gender I identify with →

360
00:21:32,325 --> 00:21:35,762
I started thinking about it. (Ryoko) Wow.

361
00:21:35,828 --> 00:21:39,265
(Luna) But it varies from person to person.

362
00:21:39,332 --> 00:21:41,768
If there were 100 transgender people →

363
00:21:41,834 --> 00:21:45,772
There are 100 ways of thinking and making decisions.

364
00:21:45,838 --> 00:21:48,775
(Ryoko) From various options→

365
00:21:48,841 --> 00:21:52,779
Mom chose to be who she is now.

366
00:21:52,845 --> 00:21:58,718
(Luna) Yes, no matter what anyone says, I want to stick to what I have decided to do.

367
00:21:58,785 --> 00:22:02,722
I don't think that decision was wrong.

368
00:22:02,789 --> 00:22:07,226
(Ryoko) I see... that's cool.

369
00:22:07,293 --> 00:22:11,731
(Luna) I just happened to be blessed.

370
00:22:11,798 --> 00:22:16,235
I was able to find a way to live as a bar mom.

371
00:22:16,302 --> 00:22:19,739
I can’t see a future in which I can live as a transgender →

372
00:22:19,806 --> 00:22:22,809
There are many people suffering.

373
00:22:29,315 --> 00:22:32,752
(Kikuo) I just bought a hamburger.

374
00:22:32,819 --> 00:22:35,755
(Atsushi) I did it. I'm hungry.

375
00:22:35,822 --> 00:22:37,757
What are you doing?

376
00:22:37,824 --> 00:22:40,259
Oh, were you trying to cook rice?

377
00:22:40,326 --> 00:22:43,763
(Atsushi) That's what I thought, but I still don't really understand.

378
00:22:43,830 --> 00:22:45,765
(Kikuo) Let's eat that rice at night.

379
00:22:45,832 --> 00:22:48,334
Dad will make fried rice or something.

380
00:22:50,336 --> 00:22:52,839
Aroma: How about a hamburger? (Fragrance) I don't need it.

381
00:22:54,273 --> 00:22:57,710
What? That's it. >> It's your own fault, isn't it?

382
00:22:57,777 --> 00:22:59,779
(Kikuo) Huh?

383
00:23:06,786 --> 00:23:11,224
Sato Shoten is an antique store.

384
00:23:11,290 --> 00:23:14,227
(Luna) Oh, that's nice.

385
00:23:14,293 --> 00:23:18,231
Speaking of antiques, I think of Mr. Masuji Ibuse's ``Chinhindo Shushu''.

386
00:23:18,297 --> 00:23:22,802
Tomomi Muramatsu's ``Jidaiya no Wife'' was also good.

387
00:23:24,303 --> 00:23:26,739
(Male) Well, if you have any questions, please contact the police station.

388
00:23:26,806 --> 00:23:29,308
(Sato) Yes, thank you.

389
00:23:31,310 --> 00:23:33,312
(Sato) Welcome.

390
00:23:35,314 --> 00:23:37,750
(Sato) Ah, just now, detective.

391
00:23:37,817 --> 00:23:41,821
(Ryoko) Huh? Did something happen? >> I got burglarized.

392
00:23:49,529 --> 00:23:54,467
(Luna) So this lamp and this clock →

393
00:23:54,534 --> 00:23:56,969
I'll take this telephone object.

394
00:23:57,036 --> 00:23:59,539
>> I see...!? Ah, thank you!

395
00:24:02,041 --> 00:24:04,477
(sound of calculating on a calculator)

396
00:24:04,544 --> 00:24:07,980
It will be 5,103,000 yen.

397
00:24:08,047 --> 00:24:11,484
(Luna) Please. >> Thank you.

398
00:24:11,551 --> 00:24:15,488
(Luna) Don't you know the man named Kazuto Sato?

399
00:24:15,555 --> 00:24:17,490
>> Kazuto Sato…｡

400
00:24:17,557 --> 00:24:20,993
No, I don't know.

401
00:24:21,060 --> 00:24:24,497
There are many Satos all over Japan.

402
00:24:24,564 --> 00:24:26,499
I'm sorry, but I bought a lot →

403
00:24:26,566 --> 00:24:28,000
I can't help you.

404
00:24:28,067 --> 00:24:32,438
(Luna) No, I'm happy to have found something so valuable.

405
00:24:32,505 --> 00:24:34,941
>>Customers have great eyesight!

406
00:24:35,007 --> 00:24:38,444
I didn't do anything to sell the burglary.

407
00:24:38,511 --> 00:24:42,949
(Ryoko) So, only cash was taken? >> No, no money was taken.

408
00:24:43,015 --> 00:24:45,451
Only the shield is missing.

409
00:24:45,518 --> 00:24:47,453
(Ryoko) Shield?

410
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:49,956
>>At a party at the Osaka Chamber of Commerce and Industry→

411
00:24:50,022 --> 00:24:54,460
It was a souvenir given out to the store celebrating its 70th anniversary.

412
00:24:54,894 --> 00:24:56,629
(Luna) What kind of shield is it?

413
00:24:56,696 --> 00:24:58,631
>>Ah.

414
00:24:58,698 --> 00:25:02,702
There's nothing unusual about this, right?

415
00:25:04,203 --> 00:25:06,639
Ah, that's right, this person→

416
00:25:06,706 --> 00:25:10,142
He was robbed and killed after a party.

417
00:25:10,209 --> 00:25:12,645
(Ryoko) Ah, I saw it on the news.

418
00:25:12,712 --> 00:25:17,149
>> We got away with empty nesting, but I wonder what would have happened if we had run into each other.

419
00:25:17,216 --> 00:25:18,651
(Ryoko) Ah!

420
00:25:18,718 --> 00:25:22,154
I went to this grandma's shop a while ago.

421
00:25:22,221 --> 00:25:24,156
>> Mr. Sato Shokai.

422
00:25:24,223 --> 00:25:27,660
We often get confused because our names are similar.

423
00:25:27,727 --> 00:25:31,664
The landlady was a nice person, wasn't she? Classy and kind.

424
00:25:31,731 --> 00:25:34,166
(Ryoko) Huh... Are you kind?

425
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:38,671
>> But contrary to his appearance, he's actually strong at heart.

426
00:25:38,738 --> 00:25:42,675
I've been protecting that store ever since my husband passed away.

427
00:25:42,742 --> 00:25:46,178
It seems like my grandchild comes to help me sometimes.

428
00:25:46,245 --> 00:25:49,181
I think it will be very difficult at that age.

429
00:25:49,248 --> 00:25:51,684
(Ryoko) Your grandchild was here just now.

430
00:25:51,751 --> 00:25:55,688
>> Nori-kun was there? He's a good kid too.

431
00:25:55,755 --> 00:25:59,692
I guess the proprietress is worried about standing in the store alone.

432
00:25:59,759 --> 00:26:03,195
(Ryoko) If you can't see, you must be in some way inconvenient.

433
00:26:03,262 --> 00:26:05,197
>> Huh? Can't you see?

434
00:26:05,264 --> 00:26:09,702
Landlady: I ​​still love reading to the point where I go to used bookstores.

435
00:26:09,769 --> 00:26:13,272
It seems like you like foreign novels.

436
00:26:14,774 --> 00:26:19,211
Ah, but I guess I haven't been able to see it very well lately.

437
00:26:19,278 --> 00:26:22,715
It looked like it was going to be hard to get home from the party the other day.

438
00:26:22,782 --> 00:26:24,717
(Luna) What happened?

439
00:26:24,784 --> 00:26:27,720
(Sato's voice) A man running on the road at night bumps into me...

440
00:26:27,787 --> 00:26:29,221
[Landlady, are you okay? ]

441
00:26:29,288 --> 00:26:32,725
(Sato's voice) I was having trouble picking up my scattered luggage.

442
00:26:36,228 --> 00:26:39,665
(Luna) Sato Shoten Sato Shokai…｡

443
00:26:39,732 --> 00:26:42,668
Sato Shoten Sato Shokai…｡

444
00:26:42,735 --> 00:26:45,171
(Ryoko) What happened?

445
00:26:45,237 --> 00:26:46,739
(Luna) No.

446
00:26:50,743 --> 00:26:53,179
(Luna) One grilled sweet potato, please. >> Thank you.

447
00:26:53,245 --> 00:26:54,747
(Ryoko) Are you still eating?

448
00:26:59,251 --> 00:27:02,188
(Ryoko) "Shunkinsho".

449
00:27:02,254 --> 00:27:06,692
If you see the raw manuscript, you might want to read it.

450
00:27:06,759 --> 00:27:11,764
If you read it properly, you'll understand Sasuke's feelings.

451
00:27:17,770 --> 00:27:26,212
♪～

452
00:27:27,013 --> 00:27:28,781
(Luna) 《Shopkeeper with a white cane》

453
00:27:28,848 --> 00:27:32,718
>> [I can't see you, but I can't tell from your voice. Come out now! ]

454
00:27:32,785 --> 00:27:34,720
(Luna) 《Stolen Shield》

455
00:27:34,787 --> 00:27:38,224
>> [The house was burglarized and only the shield was missing]

456
00:27:38,290 --> 00:27:40,726
(Luna) 《A kimono shop with a nice scent》

457
00:27:40,793 --> 00:27:42,728
(Ryoko) [I've become sensitive to smells]

458
00:27:42,795 --> 00:27:44,730
(Luna) 《Sasuke's feelings》

459
00:27:44,797 --> 00:27:48,801
(Ryoko) [Was it necessary for Sasuke to hurt himself? ]

460
00:27:51,804 --> 00:27:53,806
(Luna) We are connected.

461
00:27:55,307 --> 00:27:58,244
We were protected.

462
00:27:58,310 --> 00:28:00,312
(Ryoko) What do you mean?

463
00:28:04,817 --> 00:28:08,754
(Luna) Mr. Tamura Where are you now? I want you to check something as soon as possible.

464
00:28:08,821 --> 00:28:11,257
(Tamura) Huh?

465
00:28:11,323 --> 00:28:13,325
I understand.

466
00:28:14,827 --> 00:28:17,763
(Luna) Let's hurry before the worst happens.

467
00:28:17,830 --> 00:28:19,331
(Ryoko) Yes.

468
00:28:24,804 --> 00:28:28,741
(Luna) Sorry! I'm the one you asked about earlier!

469
00:28:28,808 --> 00:28:35,247
(sound of shutter opening)

470
00:28:35,314 --> 00:28:38,584
What happened? (Luna) I'd like to talk to the landlady.

471
00:28:38,651 --> 00:28:40,219
>> Ah, just a moment...

472
00:28:40,286 --> 00:28:43,722
(Luna) Landlady! Now from the antique shop Sato Shoten →

473
00:28:43,789 --> 00:28:46,726
I heard that the landlady likes books.

474
00:28:46,792 --> 00:28:50,229
I would like to give you a book by Kathryn Stockett.

475
00:28:50,296 --> 00:28:52,731
>> Could you pick it up? It's already closed today.

476
00:28:52,798 --> 00:28:56,302
(Yoriko) \Kathryn Stockett is great/

477
00:28:57,303 --> 00:28:59,738
(Whoosh) Ugh!

478
00:28:59,805 --> 00:29:01,740
What are you doing...!

479
00:29:01,807 --> 00:29:04,743
(Injection sound) Wow...!

480
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:07,246
Ha ha... (Luna) Ryoko-san!

481
00:29:07,313 --> 00:29:08,814
(Ryoko) Huh?

482
00:29:10,316 --> 00:29:11,817
>> Ah!

483
00:29:13,319 --> 00:29:16,689
(scream)

484
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:35,708
♪～

485
00:29:35,775 --> 00:29:38,277
Yes, yes... stay still.

486
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:41,714
Stay still.

487
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:47,219
(Ryoko) Huh... that's good. >> Ah, Ookini, Ookini.

488
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:50,222
(Luna) I'm glad you're safe. Please come here.

489
00:29:50,289 --> 00:29:54,727
>> Oh, I'm sorry, ha...

490
00:29:54,794 --> 00:29:58,731
(Luna) Landlady, you can actually see it, right?

491
00:29:58,797 --> 00:30:00,232
(Ryoko) Huh?

492
00:30:00,299 --> 00:30:04,737
(Luna) When I first arrived, I was interested in that white cane.

493
00:30:04,803 --> 00:30:09,241
Normally, the length of a white cane is from the ground to the armpit.

494
00:30:09,308 --> 00:30:13,746
Or, the standard height is minus 43cm →

495
00:30:13,813 --> 00:30:16,682
That white cane is too long.

496
00:30:16,749 --> 00:30:20,519
>>It's my deceased husband's.

497
00:30:20,586 --> 00:30:23,022
I can see my eyes.

498
00:30:23,088 --> 00:30:27,026
(Ryoko) Well, then why?

499
00:30:27,092 --> 00:30:30,529
(Luna) Don't let any harm come to us.

500
00:30:30,596 --> 00:30:32,531
...Isn't it?

501
00:30:32,598 --> 00:30:38,103
>> This man came to the store a little while ago when the two of us were there...

502
00:30:42,608 --> 00:30:46,045
(Yoriko's voice) I knew it was a robbery targeting elderly people →

503
00:30:46,111 --> 00:30:49,114
I immediately pretended to be blind.

504
00:30:50,616 --> 00:30:55,554
[Nori-kun? It's been a while]

505
00:30:55,621 --> 00:31:04,563
♪～

506
00:31:04,630 --> 00:31:09,068
[It was cold, wasn't it?]

507
00:31:09,134 --> 00:31:11,570
(Yoriko's voice) Pretending that I mistook you for my grandson→

508
00:31:11,637 --> 00:31:14,573
I decided to live it up until I had enough money.

509
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:16,508
(Luna) [Sorry]

510
00:31:16,575 --> 00:31:20,012
(Yoriko's voice) At that time, you and others appeared →

511
00:31:20,079 --> 00:31:24,516
We can't involve our customers.

512
00:31:24,583 --> 00:31:27,019
(Ryoko) That's right.

513
00:31:27,086 --> 00:31:31,023
(Luna) Thank you for protecting me.

514
00:31:31,090 --> 00:31:33,525
>> I'm determined.

515
00:31:33,592 --> 00:31:37,029
(Luna) Looks like you haven't found what you're looking for yet.

516
00:31:37,096 --> 00:31:39,031
(Ryoko) What are you looking for?

517
00:31:39,098 --> 00:31:41,033
(Tamura) Is that so? (Luna) Yes.

518
00:31:41,100 --> 00:31:46,038
The 70th anniversary commemorative shield is the weapon used in the robbery and murder.

519
00:31:46,105 --> 00:31:48,540
(Tamura) I spoke to the victim's family.

520
00:31:48,607 --> 00:31:53,045
It seems that the shield he received at the party is nowhere to be found.

521
00:31:53,112 --> 00:31:57,116
(Luna) Because you brought it home, right? After the crime.

522
00:31:59,118 --> 00:32:03,122
If I were to write a novel based on this incident...

523
00:32:05,124 --> 00:32:07,059
(Osawa) [Hey! ]

524
00:32:07,126 --> 00:32:10,129
[What are you doing? ]

525
00:32:13,132 --> 00:32:15,567
(Osawa) [Don't let me escape! ]

526
00:32:15,634 --> 00:32:17,503
[Sound of hitting]

527
00:32:17,569 --> 00:32:21,006
(Luna's voice) While running away, he collides with the landlady →

528
00:32:21,073 --> 00:32:25,010
I mistook two shields of the same shape in the dark.

529
00:32:25,077 --> 00:32:30,015
Later, he realized that he had to get the murder weapon back.

530
00:32:30,082 --> 00:32:34,520
If a shield with your fingerprints or the victim's blood is found →

531
00:32:34,586 --> 00:32:36,522
Because it's over.

532
00:32:36,588 --> 00:32:38,524
However, he made a mistake →

533
00:32:38,590 --> 00:32:44,029
Sneak into Sato Shoten, an antique store with a similar name to Sato Shokai→

534
00:32:44,096 --> 00:32:48,534
I brought home the shield, still in the paper bag.

535
00:32:48,600 --> 00:32:52,037
What remained in my hand were two unrelated shields.

536
00:32:52,104 --> 00:32:53,539
>> [Shit...]

537
00:32:53,605 --> 00:32:57,042
(Luna's voice) He came here to retrieve the murder weapon this time.

538
00:32:57,109 --> 00:33:01,046
(Ryoko) He's a rather harried criminal.

539
00:33:01,113 --> 00:33:04,550
(Tamura) I will listen to your story slowly at the police station.

540
00:33:04,616 --> 00:33:08,053
>> Hey! Hey...!

541
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:10,122
Just kidding!

542
00:33:17,129 --> 00:33:19,565
(Tamura) Stop it! Stop it, hey!

543
00:33:20,399 --> 00:33:22,835
>> Don't underestimate anyone!

544
00:33:22,901 --> 00:33:24,837
(Kominato) Oh... calm down!

545
00:33:24,903 --> 00:33:27,339
Hahahaha...

546
00:33:27,406 --> 00:33:30,342
(Jet sound) (Wail)

547
00:33:30,409 --> 00:33:31,844
(Yoriko) Huh…｡

548
00:33:31,910 --> 00:33:36,415
What are you doing to my store?

549
00:33:38,417 --> 00:33:42,354
How many digestive organs do you have? (Yoriko) You idiot!

550
00:33:42,421 --> 00:33:44,356
I'm mad!

551
00:33:44,423 --> 00:33:46,358
(2 people) Seriously...?

552
00:33:46,425 --> 00:33:48,861
This kimono shop is my husband →

553
00:33:48,927 --> 00:33:52,364
It was built through a lot of bloody hardship!

554
00:33:52,431 --> 00:33:56,368
The two of us have overcome both hardships and joys together.

555
00:33:56,435 --> 00:34:00,806
This store is filled with such precious memories!

556
00:34:00,873 --> 00:34:05,310
You can't do anything about that!

557
00:34:05,377 --> 00:34:08,881
Hurry up! This idiot!

558
00:34:11,383 --> 00:34:14,887
(Tamura) First of all, he is the current offender for arrest and confinement and attempted arson.

559
00:34:20,392 --> 00:34:24,329
(Ryoko) Are you okay? (Luna) Are you hurt?

560
00:34:24,396 --> 00:34:27,833
>> I can't bear it. I'm trying to get involved.

561
00:34:27,900 --> 00:34:31,403
(Ryoko) I'm glad you're safe.

562
00:34:36,408 --> 00:34:39,344
(siren)

563
00:34:39,411 --> 00:34:51,857
♪～

564
00:34:51,924 --> 00:34:55,360
That man asked me where the shield was.

565
00:34:55,427 --> 00:34:57,863
I hid it immediately.

566
00:35:00,866 --> 00:35:06,305
I really wanted to offer it to the Buddhist altar on the anniversary of my husband's death tomorrow.

567
00:35:06,371 --> 00:35:12,377
He managed to protect the store 10 years after he passed away.

568
00:35:13,579 --> 00:35:16,515
(Tamura) I'll take you to the hospital. >> No need, no need.

569
00:35:16,582 --> 00:35:21,019
There's no pain anywhere, and I have to clean up the store.

570
00:35:21,086 --> 00:35:25,090
(Ryoko) Well then, we'll help you clean up.

571
00:35:29,094 --> 00:35:33,599
(Tamura) Well, it's already late, so I'll come back to talk to you tomorrow.

572
00:35:35,601 --> 00:35:39,538
>> I'm sorry for making the customer do something like this.

573
00:35:39,605 --> 00:35:42,541
(Luna) This is also a coincidence, so don't worry about it.

574
00:35:42,608 --> 00:35:46,044
>> Hahaha…｡ (Ryoko) Hey, now that I think about it, about that →

575
00:35:46,111 --> 00:35:49,047
Kathryn Sto... What is blah?

576
00:35:49,114 --> 00:35:52,551
(Luna) Kathryn Stockett is an American novelist.

577
00:35:52,618 --> 00:35:56,054
His representative work is ``Help.''

578
00:35:56,121 --> 00:35:59,491
(Ryoko) Aha... I see.

579
00:35:59,558 --> 00:36:04,496
>> That's right, I couldn't imagine anyone using the code.

580
00:36:04,563 --> 00:36:06,999
You did a great job of reasoning, too.

581
00:36:07,065 --> 00:36:09,501
Can you become Agatha Christie?

582
00:36:09,568 --> 00:36:13,005
(Ryoko) Haha, she's aiming to become a writer.

583
00:36:13,071 --> 00:36:17,009
>> Really? No wonder it's such a big deal.

584
00:36:17,075 --> 00:36:21,013
(Luna) Ryoko also gave me a hint. (Ryoko) Eh, me?

585
00:36:21,079 --> 00:36:23,515
[Sasuke just pretends he can't see →

586
00:36:23,582 --> 00:36:25,517
Isn't that good? ]

587
00:36:25,584 --> 00:36:29,021
(Luna) What if the landlady pretended that she couldn't see?→

588
00:36:29,087 --> 00:36:34,026
When I thought about the reason, I felt a sense of discomfort towards him.

589
00:36:34,092 --> 00:36:36,528
(Ryoko) Do you feel uncomfortable? (Luna) Perfume.

590
00:36:36,595 --> 00:36:39,531
(Ryoko) [Grandchild? It smelled good]

591
00:36:39,598 --> 00:36:43,035
(Luna) Staff at a kimono store don't wear perfume.

592
00:36:43,101 --> 00:36:46,038
Because the smell transfers to the items. (Ryoko) Ah.

593
00:36:46,104 --> 00:36:49,041
(Luna) And he was also wearing a ring.

594
00:36:49,107 --> 00:36:51,543
There is a possibility of damaging the product →

595
00:36:51,610 --> 00:36:54,546
Employees at kimono stores don't wear accessories.

596
00:36:54,613 --> 00:37:00,485
>> That's right. It's true.

597
00:37:00,552 --> 00:37:03,989
(Ryoko) I hope it was even a little helpful.

598
00:37:04,056 --> 00:37:05,991
>> Wait a minute.

599
00:37:06,058 --> 00:37:08,994
What would have happened if the two of you were not there?

600
00:37:09,061 --> 00:37:14,566
I'm sure my husband is feeling relieved in heaven too.

601
00:37:18,570 --> 00:37:21,006
(Luna) Oh, are you your husband?

602
00:37:21,073 --> 00:37:24,009
>> Yeah, yeah, he's a guy, right?

603
00:37:24,076 --> 00:37:27,012
(Luna) Very. (Ryoko) The landlady is also beautiful.

604
00:37:27,079 --> 00:37:29,014
>> Hahaha…｡

605
00:37:29,081 --> 00:37:33,018
My husband and I are eloping.

606
00:37:33,085 --> 00:37:38,023
Well, because of that, many people pointed at me →

607
00:37:38,090 --> 00:37:40,525
It did interfere with my business.

608
00:37:40,592 --> 00:37:44,529
The owner is Nako’s shop and our house →

609
00:37:44,596 --> 00:37:49,034
Hehehehe I said I spent my life protecting it...

610
00:37:49,101 --> 00:37:51,036
Ah, Akan, no, no.

611
00:37:51,103 --> 00:37:55,040
It's an old story, but please be patient.

612
00:37:55,107 --> 00:37:59,478
(Ryoko) No, thank you for your wonderful story.

613
00:37:59,544 --> 00:38:02,481
(Luna) Ah, that's right, I'd like to make a kimono →

614
00:38:02,547 --> 00:38:06,485
Could you please model me? >> Do you like kimono?

615
00:38:06,551 --> 00:38:08,987
(Luna) Yes, I run a bar→

616
00:38:09,054 --> 00:38:10,989
I often serve customers in kimono.

617
00:38:11,056 --> 00:38:13,992
>> Ah, really, just wait a minute.

618
00:38:14,059 --> 00:38:17,562
I'm looking for the perfect one hahaha...

619
00:38:24,569 --> 00:38:29,007
(Luna) As expected from a long-established kimono shop, they had some great items.

620
00:38:29,074 --> 00:38:32,010
(Ryoko) Mom, how much did you spend in total today?

621
00:38:32,077 --> 00:38:38,016
(Luna) Well, a lot of things happened so I forgot.

622
00:38:38,083 --> 00:38:42,020
(Ryoko) It's true that a lot of things happened.

623
00:38:42,087 --> 00:38:47,526
We talked about many things and thought about many things.

624
00:38:47,592 --> 00:38:51,029
(Luna) What did you think about?

625
00:38:51,096 --> 00:38:56,535
(Ryoko) An unwavering feeling that sticks through no matter what anyone says.

626
00:38:56,601 --> 00:39:01,473
That landlady and Sasuke from Shunkinsho.

627
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:04,976
(Luna) Isn't that what happened to Kazuto-san as well?

628
00:39:05,043 --> 00:39:08,980
Just like the landlady risked her life to protect the store →

629
00:39:09,047 --> 00:39:11,550
He also protected Ryoko.

630
00:39:14,052 --> 00:39:19,558
(Ryoko) Huh... There's more to that story.

631
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:28,066
Two months after that fire, we suddenly broke up.

632
00:39:29,568 --> 00:39:34,072
>> [I will return to Osaka after graduation]

633
00:39:35,574 --> 00:39:41,012
[I decided to marry her and take over my parents' business]

634
00:39:41,079 --> 00:39:44,015
(Ryoko) [Wait a minute, what do you mean? ]

635
00:39:44,082 --> 00:39:46,017
>> [I'm really sorry]

636
00:39:46,084 --> 00:39:49,588
[But it's already been decided]

637
00:39:56,094 --> 00:40:02,467
(Ryoko) [Do you think you can understand why someone suddenly said something like that? ]

638
00:40:02,534 --> 00:40:07,038
>> [I no longer have any love for you]

639
00:40:09,541 --> 00:40:11,977
(Ryoko) I couldn't forgive you.

640
00:40:12,043 --> 00:40:16,982
I didn't think he was the kind of person who would do something like that.

641
00:40:17,048 --> 00:40:23,054
But I just can't believe it.

642
00:40:24,055 --> 00:40:31,563
(Custom) [Love is risking your life, I don't think it's naive]

643
00:40:33,064 --> 00:40:36,568
[...Is that too cool?]

644
00:40:39,571 --> 00:40:42,507
[No matter what anyone says→

645
00:40:42,574 --> 00:40:47,012
I think I made the best choice.]

646
00:40:47,078 --> 00:40:50,081
[I'm glad Ryoko is safe]

647
00:40:52,584 --> 00:40:55,587
(Ryoko) What's up with that Kazuto?

648
00:40:58,089 --> 00:41:02,527
I can't digest it for a long time.

649
00:41:02,594 --> 00:41:04,596
Ever since that day.

650
00:41:08,099 --> 00:41:13,038
(Ryoko) While visiting various shops all day →

651
00:41:13,104 --> 00:41:17,542
Actually, I was really excited.

652
00:41:17,609 --> 00:41:24,049
When I think that Kazuto might be on the other side of this door...

653
00:41:24,115 --> 00:41:31,056
Ah, I want to meet Kazuto more than I thought →

654
00:41:31,122 --> 00:41:34,559
I got it clear today.

655
00:41:34,626 --> 00:41:39,564
I want to meet you properly no matter what anyone says.

656
00:41:39,631 --> 00:41:43,568
I want to settle my feelings.

657
00:41:43,635 --> 00:41:51,576
So please cooperate a little more.

658
00:41:51,643 --> 00:41:53,645
please.

659
00:42:00,085 --> 00:42:06,591
(Luna) Even if God abandons me, I will believe in myself.

660
00:42:09,594 --> 00:42:14,032
(Luna) These are the words of Junichiro Tanizaki.

661
00:42:14,099 --> 00:42:18,536
If Ryoko decides to do so, let's stick to it.

662
00:42:18,603 --> 00:42:21,539
I'll help you.

663
00:42:21,606 --> 00:42:36,054
♪～

664
00:42:36,121 --> 00:42:38,056
📱(Camera shutter sound)

665
00:42:38,123 --> 00:42:49,567
♪～

666
00:42:49,634 --> 00:42:53,138
(Luna's voice) ``The princess has gone to bed.''

667
00:42:56,641 --> 00:43:00,512
(Tamura) Sato Shokai's shield that the criminal mistook was →

668
00:43:00,578 --> 00:43:02,514
We are currently searching.

669
00:43:02,580 --> 00:43:05,517
I'm sorry that I couldn't make it in time for the anniversary of your husband's death.

670
00:43:05,583 --> 00:43:10,021
>> No, just your feelings are enough.

671
00:43:10,088 --> 00:43:13,525
(Tamura) No, I will definitely find it and return it to you.

672
00:43:13,591 --> 00:43:15,527
Well then.

673
00:43:15,593 --> 00:43:20,031
>>Ah, please give my regards to those two.

674
00:43:20,098 --> 00:43:22,033
(Tamura) Yes.

675
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:26,037
Actually, the one with short hair has been my friend since high school.

676
00:43:26,104 --> 00:43:28,540
>> Well, is that so?

677
00:43:28,606 --> 00:43:32,043
You were very smart.

678
00:43:32,110 --> 00:43:37,616
(Tamura) Well, I feel like that is both a strength and a weakness.

679
00:43:41,119 --> 00:43:45,557
(Luna) It's delicious. That's good because I don't usually eat breakfast.

680
00:43:45,623 --> 00:43:47,559
(Ryoko) Good.

681
00:43:47,625 --> 00:43:51,062
It's delicious if you put this in between. (Luna) Then I'll eat it.

682
00:43:51,129 --> 00:43:54,632
(Ryoko) I need another coffee. (Luna) Yes.

683
00:43:57,135 --> 00:44:00,005
I guess she's a good mother.

684
00:44:00,071 --> 00:44:03,074
(Ryoko) Huh? (Luna) No.

685
00:44:05,577 --> 00:44:07,512
>> Good morning.

686
00:44:07,579 --> 00:44:09,514
What is that?

687
00:44:09,581 --> 00:44:12,017
I'm planning on making an omelet.

688
00:44:12,083 --> 00:44:15,520
(Atsushi) It doesn't look like an omelet. (Kikuo) If it goes into your stomach, it's the same.

689
00:44:15,587 --> 00:44:17,589
(chime)

690
00:44:21,593 --> 00:44:24,529
(Haruko) Acchan Yocchan Good morning.

691
00:44:24,596 --> 00:44:26,531
Grandma! (fragrance) Why!?

692
00:44:26,598 --> 00:44:28,533
(Haruko) Sorry for coming so suddenly.

693
00:44:28,600 --> 00:44:30,035
Ah, Kikuo-san.

694
00:44:30,101 --> 00:44:32,037
Eh, wait, grandma, what about your strained back?

695
00:44:32,103 --> 00:44:35,040
Or what about your mother? >> To?

696
00:44:35,106 --> 00:44:37,042
(Luna) Where did you buy these ingredients?

697
00:44:37,108 --> 00:44:40,545
(Ryoko) Oh, there's a convenience store nearby. (Luna) Huh?

698
00:44:40,612 --> 00:44:45,116
(Ryoko) Wasn't it delicious? (Luna) Hmm, it's delicious.
